@NODE "word_from_me" "A few choice words from me"
@TOC "MAIN"


@{b}Who are you?@{ub}

My name is Gerard Sweeney, and regular readers of YS may just remember me from
the Practical POKEs section... For the last few years of that great magazine's
life, I was one of the main hack contributors to that section (in fact, at the
end I was the only one, beside Jon North and his various pseudonymns... A
sad, but true fact)....


@{b}What on earth is this?@{ub}

Well, anyone who has bought the Limited Edition gold CD RETRO GOLD will no
doubt have found that it suffers the same problem as the other Speccy CDs
(like Speccy Sensations 1,2 & 96). In other words, there are so many
snapshots in scabby IBM 8.3 filename standard, that there are lots of
dupes, renames, and filenames which make no sense at all.

What I've done is to go through every single snapshot on my emulator and
make up a file list sorting the games in alphabetical order.


@{b}How does it work?@{UB}

Quite simply, the index is sorted alphabetically by game name (not snapshot
name, as that would have been stupid).... If you want to load a game, just
go to the appropriate letter for that game, with the exception of anything
starting with "THE", where you would go by the first letter of the second
word in the game's name....

Once there, just click on the name of the game you wish to load, and if you
use ZXAM (and if not, why not?), it will load the emulator (if not already
loaded), load the snapshot, and run the game.

However, this works slightly differently if you chose to link it with Hack
Attack III....


@{b}Hack Attack III?@{UB}

Hack Attack III is a really good POKE guide written for use with ZXAM. It has
POKEs for over 1000 games, almost all of which have been tested! It did have
one drawback however, as Rastan wrote it in such a way that you had to load
the game with the emulator, go to the POKE menu, enter the POKES, then go
back to the emulator window. Not a big hassle, but this index program runs
an AREXX program which will update all of the Hack Attack III guide files
which have a snapshot on the Retro Gold CD. It will add a "LOAD" and a
"RUN" button to the file, so that you can do it all from one window...

To achieve this, it runs a script I wrote called ZXAM_RUN.REXX which is
located in the REXX: directory. This is a complete rewrite of the original
script which came with ZXAM, which had the unfortunate side effect of not
working at all!

By all means, COPY this file into the ZXAM REXX directory, but don't MOVE
it, or else this index won't work at all!
@endnode

